The South African Weather Services says the hot temperatures are expected to last until the start of the weekend. JOHANNESBURG The Johannesburg Emergency Service has issued a warning of possible veld fires due to a heatwave expected to start today.The South African Weather Services says the hot temperatures are expected to last until the start of the weekend.Johannesburg's EMS is urging residents to keep a watchful eye on children when swimming, and to protect themselves from sun damage.Spokesperson Robert Mulaudzi says, Keep safe by making sure that if it s possible they stay away from direct sunlight between 11am and 3pm in the afternoon. (Edited by Neo Koza)